name: Counterpart
overview: Howard Silk is a lowly cog in a bureaucratic UN agency who is turning the last corner of a life filled with regret when he discovers the agency he works for is guarding a secret: a crossing to a parallel dimension.

seasons.name: Season 2
seasons.overview: Season two finds the Crossing closed and each Howard stranded in the other's world. As a cold war escalates between worlds and deepens the divide, both men find themselves growing increasingly like the other.

tagline: What if there were another you?

episodes.name: The Crossing
episodes.overview: Howard Silk discovers the truth about where he works. The Office of Interchange searches for an assassin.

episodes.name: Birds of a Feather
episodes.overview: Howard must work together with his counterpart. Baldwin comes face to face with her past. Emily, from the other side, tries to make sense of her orders.

episodes.name: The Lost Art of Diplomacy
episodes.overview: Both sides turn to diplomacy to resolve a conflict. Emily obtains a special visa. Howard interrogates a suspect.

episodes.name: Both Sides Now
episodes.overview: Both Howards deepen their investigation of the conspiracy. Quayle meets one of Howard's sources. Clare must decide what to do about Baldwin.

episodes.name: Shaking the Tree
episodes.overview: Howard discovers another side of Emily. Howard and Emily search for answers about a mysterious drop site. Aldrich and Quayle seek intel from an old friend.

episodes.name: Act Like You've Been Here Before
episodes.overview: Aldrich questions a not-too recent death in the office. Emily, Howard and Shaw follow a lead.

episodes.name: The Sincerest Form of Flattery
episodes.overview: Clare's past is revealed. Quayle suffers through his own birthday party.

episodes.name: Love the Lie
episodes.overview: The aftermath of the Indigo school discovery takes an emotional toll. Quayle grapples with his wife's new identity.

episodes.name: No Man's Land (1)
episodes.overview: Howard attempts to thwart the Guest's plans. Howard and Emily chase Kaspar.

episodes.name: No Man's Land (2)
episodes.overview: A crisis at the O.I. leaves both Howards stranded.

episodes.name: Inside Out
episodes.overview: While hiding in Howard’s life, Howard Prime must avoid detection at home and at the OI. Quayle and Clare struggle to adjust to their new arrangement.

episodes.name: Outside In
episodes.overview: Imprisoned on the Other Side, Howard's loyalties are tested. Emily Prime gets a promotion.

episodes.name: Something Borrowed
episodes.overview: Howard is transferred to a mysterious prison called Echo. An unexpected visit gives Emily a connection to her old life. Emily Prime and Shaw's investigation is met with resistance.

episodes.name: Point of Departure
episodes.overview: Howard Prime, Quayle and Clare must unite against a common enemy. Emily Prime turns her investigation towards her other. Yanek probes Howard's past.

episodes.name: Shadow Puppets
episodes.overview: A new revelation puts Howard Prime and Quayle in jeopardy. Life at Echo is disrupted. Clare reconnects with her past.

episodes.name: Twin Cities
episodes.overview: The origins of the Crossing are revealed.

episodes.name: No Strings Attached
episodes.overview: The fallout of the lockdown casts suspicions around the OI. Howard and Emily Prime find clues about the history of Management. Clare questions her allegiances.

episodes.name: In from the Cold
episodes.overview: Howard Prime and Emily work together to figure out Indigo's plans. Clare and Quayle consider their future. Howard must face the truth about his wife.

episodes.name: You to You
episodes.overview: Management makes a historic decision. Emily sends a warning. Quayle, Clare and Temple investigate the final Indigo cell. Howard Prime reaches out to an old contact.

episodes.name: Better Angels
episodes.overview: Mira's looming threat forges some unlikely alliances.
